programmes.show_description: An extended edition of the show. Jimmy Carr, Sean Lock and Jon Richardson are joined by Nick Grimshaw, Peter Serafinowicz, Daniel Sloss and Rachel Riley.
An extended edition of the show. Jimmy Carr, Sean Lock and Jon Richardson are joined by Dr Christian Jessen, Kimberley Walsh, Russell Kane and Josh Widdicombe.
Jimmy Carr hosts the topical comedy show as Jamie Laing, Jessica Knappett, Rose Matafeo and Geoff Norcott join team captains Rob Beckett and Katherine Ryan.
Teleshopping
Teleshopping
YouTube star and internet sensation Bethany Mota adopts a disguise to go undercover and meet up-and-coming social media hopefuls who are trying to break through.
American football star Deion Sanders goes undercover, disguised as a businessman who hopes to start a youth football programme, to meet inspiring sports coaches and worthy fans.
In Nottingham, there are experimental menus, a compost loo and a stately home, as three couples - including competitive accountants and sustainable food growers - go head to head.
In Glasgow, Melanie and David's Celtic-fusion food takes on the two Kennys' Mexican menu, and Ami and Stuart's Scottish cuisine, in a week featuring bagpipes and an awkward confrontation.
Selling: Can the brother's sculpt a remarkable renovation for artist Laura and car collector Ken as they race to find the perfect home?
The One with All the Kangaroos: For his wedding reception, Paddy transforms a tent in a country pub car park into a mock-up of the Australian bar where he and bride-to-be Breda first met.
The Game of Thrones One: Game of Thrones fan Owen dreams of a windswept mountain landscape for his wedding ceremony. Will his bride Lisa be happy to arrive on horseback, sporting a cloak?
This episode follows Dippin' Dots, which sells cryogenically frozen beads of ice cream. CEO Scott Fischer wants to see if his empire has the manpower to cope with expansion.
Anytime Fitness is a global firm, and it's the job of brand president Stacy Anderson to keep this gym giant in shape. Are all the employees on board with the planned changes?
Barefoot Bob's: Gordon visits Barefoot Bob's beachside restaurant in Massachusetts, where husband and wife Marc and Lisa struggle to attract customers during the winter months.
Gordon revisits Caf√© Hon in Baltimore, Chiarella's in Philadelphia, and Leone's in New Jersey, to find out whether the owners have taken his advice on board.
...and Selling: Brand new series: Greg and Kristin have no time for house hunting. So Jonathan and Drew's next mission is to find a six-bedroom home on a restricted budget.
Cheers to Boobies: The crew pull off a second talent show for the returning guests. Chase has a little too much to drink, which makes Lucy lose her cool.
The series reaches its majestic climax. Who will win Greg Davies' coveted golden head and become only the seventh Taskmaster champion in history?
Jimmy Carr hosts as Sean Lock and Roisin Conaty take on Jon Richardson and Nish Kumar. Adam Buxton joins Susie Dent in Dictionary Corner. With Rachel Riley.
Jimmy Carr hosts as Sean Lock and David O'Doherty take on Jon Richardson and Natasia Demetriou. John Kearns joins Susie Dent in Dictionary Corner. With Rachel Riley.
Statham is unusually cheerful, but it will probably end in tears. Mac finds it hard to adjust to his new role, Martin hires a private detective and Caroline has a hot date.
Talented tattoo artists transform extreme inking disasters into walking works of art, starting with Ryan's bad holiday ink and Adam's lasting reminder of his ex.

Teleshopping
Singer-songwriter, actor and author Jewel dons a disguise as an event planner to go undercover and meet talented musicians and artists who are struggling to get their big break.
Stephanie McMahon, former women's champion and current chief brand officer of the WWE, goes undercover to meet aspiring wrestlers and fans and help make their dreams a reality.
In Somerset, Jacqueline and Stephen's taste of the Med competes with Jess and Fred's Portuguese menu, and Rob and Simon's homegrown grub, in a week featuring dancing and a royal revelation.
In Newcastle, Sharna and Silvar serve up family favourites and a song and dance. Charlotte and Russ plan an Italian feast. And Shannon and Max take their rival diners on a culinary journey.
...Selling: Ex footballer Adesola and his wife Jennifer are hoping for that winning feeling by scoring a big sale. When a key deal falls through, there's some last-minute drama...
The One in a Furniture Store: Celina wants an elegant, intimate wedding in a historical building, but Ben has other ideas. He has visions of them saying 'I do' in a huge furniture store.
The One with the DIY Wedding Dress: Nikki dreams of getting married in the lap of luxury, somewhere warm and indoors, but Jamie wants to create his own Wedfest at a glamping site.
TGI Fridays is one of the biggest restaurant chains. CEO Ray Blanchette wants to re-energise the brand, so he goes undercover to find out what staff think of his changes.
Xavier Mufraggi, the CEO of Club Med North America, goes undercover, disguised as a laid-back surfer, in his own resorts, to see the impact that his growth plans are having.
Olde Hitching Post: Gordon visits the historic Olde Hitching Post restaurant in Massachusetts. Tom bought the business for his daughter but refuses to let her run it.
Levanti's: Gordon visits Pennsylvania, where he meets siblings whose inability to work together is risking their father's life savings at his Italian restaurant, Levanti's.
...and Selling: Brand new series: Sunita and David face time constraints and significant sacrifices to try and buy a cheaper home. But will Sunita sign on the dotted line?
Love Boat: The guests are greatly pleased when Captain Glenn dresses up for their themed dinner. Gary struggles with his feelings about Colin and Daisy hooking.
The race continues for Taskmaster Greg Davies' golden head trophy. Lou Sanders acquires some creepy facial hair.
Jimmy Carr hosts as Sean Lock and David Mitchell go up against Jon Richardson and Katherine Ryan. The Brett Domino Trio join Susie Dent in Dictionary Corner. With Rachel Riley.
Jimmy Carr hosts as Claudia Winkleman and Johnny Vegas take on Jon Richardson and Reginald D Hunter. Sara Pascoe joins Susie Dent in Dictionary Corner. With Rachel Riley.
Caroline has to be cruel to be kind, while Joanna and Statham struggle to conceal the incident with the stuffed heron. Sue turns private dick and Martin comes into some money.
